# BADALY PROJECT — AI ASSISTANT CONTEXT
# بدالي — AI Phone Call Proxy
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## WHO YOU ARE
You are a Staff-Level Full-Stack Engineer helping finalize "Badaly" (بدالي),
a demo-ready AI phone assistant app. The presentation is TOMORROW.
Be direct, fast, and practical. No theory. Only working code.

---

## WHAT THIS PROJECT IS

**Badaly** = "instead of me" in Arabic.
Problem: Egyptians waste 15-40 minutes on hold with telecoms/banks.
Solution: AI calls customer service, navigates IVR, waits on hold,
and warm-transfers to the user's real phone when a human agent answers.

Core technology: **Retell AI** handles outbound calling + DTMF navigation
+ Voice Activity Detection (human vs hold music) + call_transfer tool.

---

## PROJECT FILES

```
badaly-backend/
├── server.js          ← Express backend. Triggers Retell API calls.
├── package.json       ← deps: express, cors, dotenv
├── .env               ← SECRET KEYS (never commit). Fill from RETELL_SETUP.md
├── .env.example       ← Template showing all required variables
├── HTML_PATCH.md      ← 4 surgical changes to apply to the frontend HTML
└── RETELL_SETUP.md    ← Step-by-step to get Retell keys
```

The frontend is: **badaly-demo__2_.html** (in this folder or parent folder)
→ A single-file Arabic PWA simulating the call flow.
→ Must be patched using HTML_PATCH.md to wire the real backend.

---

## ARCHITECTURE

```
Mobile PWA (Chrome on Android)
    │ POST /api/start-call { company, userPhone, issue }
    ▼
Node.js Express (server.js) — port 3001
    │ exposed via ngrok for phone access
    │ POST api.retellai.com/v2/call/phone-call
    ▼
Retell AI Agent
    → calls telecom/bank hotline
    → navigates IVR with DTMF tones
    → detects human voice (VAD)
    → call_transfer tool → rings user's real phone
```

**KEY INSIGHT**: The HTML simulation runs visually in parallel with the real call.
The simulation IS the demo. The real call is the magic.

---

## ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (.env)

```env
PORT=3001
RETELL_API_KEY=key_...              # Retell dashboard → Settings → API Keys
RETELL_AGENT_ID=agent_...           # URL bar when viewing agent in Retell dashboard
RETELL_FROM_NUMBER=+1...            # Phone number bought in Retell dashboard

# Egyptian company hotlines (E.164 format)
NUM_VODAFONE=+20888...
NUM_CIB=+2019666
NUM_NBE=+2019623
NUM_BANQUEMISR=+2019888
NUM_QNB=+2016000
NUM_BANQUEDUCAIRE=+2016488
```

If `.env` is missing these Retell keys → server auto-falls to **DEMO MODE**
(returns a fake callId, visual simulation still works perfectly).

---

## RETELL API CALLS

Trigger call:
```
POST https://api.retellai.com/v2/call/phone-call
Authorization: Bearer {RETELL_API_KEY}
{
  from_number: RETELL_FROM_NUMBER,
  to_number: <company hotline>,
  agent_id: RETELL_AGENT_ID,
  retell_llm_dynamic_variables: {
    user_phone: <user's Egyptian number>,
    issue_description: <what user typed>,
    company_name: <company key>
  }
}
```

Get call status:
```
GET https://api.retellai.com/v2/call/{call_id}
```

---

## COMPANIES SUPPORTED

| Key           | Arabic Name        | Shortcode | E.164 Attempt |
|---------------|--------------------|-----------|---------------|
| vodafone      | فودافون            | 888       | SIM-locked ⚠️ |
| we            | WE المصرية         | 8000      | SIM-locked ⚠️ |
| orange        | أورنج              | 110       | SIM-locked ⚠️ |
| etisalat      | إتصالات (e&)       | 333       | SIM-locked ⚠️ |
| cib           | CIB مصر            | 19666     | +2019666 ✅    |
| nbe           | البنك الأهلي       | 19623     | +2019623 ✅    |
| banquemisr    | بنك مصر            | 19888     | +2019888 ✅    |
| qnb           | QNB الأهلي         | 16000     | +2016000 ✅    |
| banqueducaire | بنك القاهرة        | 16488     | +2016488 ✅    |

**Banks (19xxx/16xxx) can be called from international numbers.**
**Telecoms (888, 8000, etc.) are SIM-locked — override with own phone for demo.**

