## RUNNING THE PROJECT

```bash
# Terminal 1 — Backend
cd badaly-backend
npm install
cp .env.example .env   # then fill in keys
node server.js

# Terminal 2 — ngrok tunnel (for phone access)
npx ngrok http 3001
# Copy the https://xxxx.ngrok-free.app URL
# → paste as BACKEND_URL in the HTML file

# Terminal 3 — Serve frontend
npx serve . -p 8080
# On phone: open Chrome → 192.168.x.x:8080/badaly-demo__2_.html
# Chrome → ⋮ → Add to Home Screen → looks like a native app
```

---

## COMMON TASKS — HOW TO HELP

**"Apply the HTML patch"**
→ Open `HTML_PATCH.md`, apply all 4 changes to `badaly-demo__2_.html`

**"Test the backend"**
→ Run: `curl http://localhost:3001/health`
→ Then: `curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/start-call -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"company":"cib","userPhone":"+201XXXXXXXXX","issue":"test"}'`

**"The server won't start"**
→ Check Node version (needs 18+ for built-in fetch): `node --version`
→ If < 18: add `node-fetch` to package.json and `const fetch = require('node-fetch')`

**"ngrok URL changes every restart"**
→ Either pay for ngrok static domain OR update `BACKEND_URL` in HTML each time
→ Alternatively: use `localtunnel`: `npx localtunnel --port 3001`

**"Retell call fires but phone doesn't ring"**
→ Check agent has `call_transfer` tool configured with `{{user_phone}}`
→ Check `userPhone` in request is E.164 format (+201XXXXXXXXX not 01XXXXXXXXX)
→ Check Retell Call History for error logs

**"Demo mode for evaluators if Retell fails"**
→ Leave `.env` empty → server returns `demoMode: true` → HTML simulation still runs
→ Tell evaluators: "The backend is integrated, here's the API response on screen"

